reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Have not used it yet, but looks and feels great
reviews.reviewText: NOTE: I have not yet travelled with this.I bought this in anticipation of upcoming travel. I wanted a carry-on that was lightweight and easy to use. I like the Delsey brand and this one looked sturdy. I received it promptly and when I opened the box and saw it was pleased with the quality. Nice sturdiness when rolling it around my house. Good wheels and easy to use and comfortable handle. The interior is spacious and I like the pockets and compartments. Excited to use it, then I will update this review.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchase this beautiful set for my three week vacation and couldn’t even use it. The two larger cases came locked. I emailed the company got no response. I spent hundreds of dollars to end up having to take my old dirty broke set and my new smaller bags. It has been two months the smaller bag handle is broke i am so disappointed. This is my fav brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I liked the spinner suitcase. It was very light and easy to maneuver.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You Had Me At Blue
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. If you're not all about the bells and whistles, then this might be it.I got the 3 piece Sky Max 2.0 CO/M/L set in blue after doing some searching and comparing different brands. Let me start by saying this is a great looking set of luggage the black accent fabric, zippers and shapes look awesome and you could get lost in the blue color. The interior of the cases has this peacock feather patterning that imo looks way better than some of the bland greys and checkerboarding of other cases. Here are the main takeaways that I wondered about when I was looking at this set:- Empty weight for 28" is 8.4lbs, 24" is 7.2lbs and carry-on is 5.7lbs- 108L capacity for 28" case, 73L for 24" case and 43L for the carry-on.- For the carry-on Delsey Paris gives internal dimensions of 19.5"x14"x9.75" with 1" of expansion. Without the spinners the external height is 20.5" (Most airlines *should* allow it).- The 28" and 24" checked bags both have TSA locks for the main compartment. The carry-on has none.- The set only has a 3 year warranty.The wheels spin and swivel effortlessly and, at least when empty, roll on carpet with little resistance. The zippers are alright, solid and I like that they color differentiated the expansion zippers in red so you don't mix them up with the others. All bags each have two front pockets, a shallow one on top and a deeper one below. The carry-on has an additional small pocket on the right side which could fit small electronics. My only gripe is the handles, the stitching seems secure but it's uneven and the handles aren't straight or center (illustrated in my pictures). The telescoping handles are also a little gritty and wobbly. Not super concerning, but I've seen other reviews note broken handles and, from what I'm seeing on mine, I wouldn't want to abuse them too much.Overall, it's a good looking and solid feeling luggage set. It doesn't come with many bells and whistles like USB, included toiletries bag, suite compartment, or internal dividers, but what it does have seems well thought out and well built.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I travel for a living, so I know how long to expect luggage to last. After my first trip with the Delsey Paris bag, it was already showing a lot of wear and tear. I didn't like it, but I was okay with that. It's a very large suitcase, which is nice, but it does allow to overpack if you're not careful. If you do get close to that 50 lb mark, it does become hard to maneuver. The handle at the top is just not strong enough. Again, that's an annoyance, but I could deal with it. But on my 2nd trip with this bag, the bolts loosened on one of the wheels and now it's just barely holding on. I managed to get it home, but it won't survive another trip. As mentioned, I travel alot and have had many suitcases over the years, and sadly, this one the worst. Just very cheaply made. I've gone through their website to see if I can get it repaired, but I'm afraid just shipping it to the closest repair center will cost more than the luggage is worth. My recommendation? Don't buy it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great size and weight!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to replace an older checked luggage piece. I love it! The color is a deep blue but not navy. It rolled perfectly down streets and in the airport. It is very lightweight. I tried multiple other brands but this one came out the best. I will def buy more of this brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not left in my mailbox
reviews.reviewText: The bag came two days early and as described. It is actually lighter than the Samsonite one I have. This one is for my daughter who needs one this size. It has nice front zip pockets and a shallow one on the top corner. It seems sturdy. The retractable handle doesn't come up as high as I thought it would but the wheels work very well. I think this should do the trick for her as an overhead compartment bag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stop shopping around and buy this set!!!!
reviews.reviewText: I looked for weeks for a set of luggage to buy to replace my old suitcases. I was headed on my eighth mission trip to Guatemala so it had to be sturdy! I actually found the set in a local store and bought it. After finding it on Amazon for $100 cheaper I returned the set and bought through Amazon. I'm happy to say the quality is identical. The set lasted through connecting flights and being thrown into the bottom of busses for travel. It took a beating and there is not a tear or fray in the fabric. The suitcases rolled easily and allowed for manipulation of multiple suitcases through the airports. I'm so impressed with this set that I plan to buy another. There are four of us in my family and we all do mission work annually in Guatemala. We needed a reliable set and this did not disappoint!

I use this bag for my first trip internationally. It appeared to be fine until I brought it home. Apparently the zipper attachments were loose and must have fallen off during the storage of the bags on the plane. I hope to get a response from Desley of how this issue can be resolved.

reviews.reviewTitle: Great quality bags however the smallest bag was missing from the order
reviews.reviewText: Great quality bags however the smallest bag was missing from the order, bags are great however super disappointed that the bag was missing. Amazons alternative was return however we threw boxes and found it to costly to repack and resend.

The stitching is uneven, one is the side zips does not open and the smallest piece is nothing like that shown in the photo. I'd return the whole lot, but it is too much effort to re-pack it all and get the box to the post office. On the whole, tacky and does not live up to the Delsey brand. The single star is awarded because the suitcases are light.
